ctl:O-7a a ctl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:label "Second-sync non-determinism: force:true breaking idempotency across the pack ecosystem" ;
    ctl:priority 1 ;
    ctl:state ctl:CLOSED ;
    ctl:nextAction "Progressively closed across 3 commits, retrofit/ggen-self-g2 and -g4: (1) 18 template frontmatters across the 8 packs crates/ggen-engine/tests/cross_pack_matrix.rs exercises (chicago-tdd-tools/clap-noun-verb/lsp-max/praxis-core/star-toml/wasm4pm-algorithms/wasm4pm-cognition/wasm4pm-compat) -- mega_project_all_packs_sync passes. (2) tcps-release-pack's 85 occurrences, zero justification found anywhere (frontmatter/pack.toml/ontology.ttl/gates/README), safety independently proven by composed_packs_e2e.rs and tcps_conformance_e2e.rs's real byte-identity assertions which do not depend on force's mis-reporting. (3) tcps-core-pack's 27 occurrences given a genuine per-file review (NOT a bulk fix, per this obligation's own prior caveat): 26 removed (same zero-justification pattern); lib.rs.tmpl's force:true kept -- confirmed load-bearing via examples/tcps-generated/tests/tcps_conformance_e2e.rs's scaffold() fn, which deliberately pre-seeds a placeholder src/lib.rs before first sync so tcps-core-pack's force:true can overwrite it; without force this would hit write.rs's FM-WRITE-005 hard-error-on-differing-content path and fail sync outright. tcps_conformance_e2e's 7/7 tests (including second_sync_is_byte_identical_idempotent) pass with the 26-file fix in place. (4) osx-clnr-pack and affidavit-pack (19 combined occurrences), per-file reviewed: both packs each carry exactly ONE genuinely documented exception -- a `*_mod_wiring.rs.tmpl` targeting `src/{osx_clnr,affidavit}_lib_wiring.rs` with an inline NOTE explaining it was retargeted off `to: src/lib.rs, inject: true` after two other packs (wasm4pm-cognition-pack/wasm4pm-facts-pack) collided on that same injected path inside examples/receiptctl, hitting write.rs's FM-WRITE-008 duplicate-output guard; force:true there is load-bearing and kept. The other 17 files (8 affidavit, 9 osx-clnr, including 5 affidavit files carrying freeze_policy:checksum) had zero documented reason -- confirmed safe to remove because write.rs's decision order runs freeze_policy:checksum's drift check (step 5) before force (step 7), so checksum-based hand-edit protection is unaffected either way; only the no-drift fall-through case changes, from force's 'always report Written' defect to the correct 'identical content -> Skipped'. Verified via composed_packs_e2e's real 2/2 pass (both packs are in its 30-pack composed set). (5) mfact-pack, mfw-pack, wasm4pm-facts-pack, tcps-ffi-pack, tcps-cli-pack, tcps-wasm-pack, tcps-std-pack, ggen-release-pack, claude-code-pack, wasm4pm-pack (30 combined occurrences): per-pack review found mfact-pack, mfw-pack, and wasm4pm-pack each carry the same one documented *_mod_wiring.rs.tmpl FM-WRITE-008 exception as affidavit/osx-clnr-pack (kept); wasm4pm-facts-pack/tcps-ffi-pack/tcps-cli-pack/tcps-wasm-pack/tcps-std-pack/ggen-release-pack/claude-code-pack have no mod_wiring file at all (no cross-pack shared-lib.rs collision risk -- tcps-ffi/cli/wasm/std each write to their OWN dedicated crates/tcps-*/ crate, not a shared consumer path) and no documented reason anywhere -- all removed. Also inspected but found ALREADY CLEAN (no fix needed, false positives from an earlier raw grep count): cargo-cicd-pack and mcpp-pack -- both packs' own pack.toml prose documents an explicit prior round that already switched their catalog/proof/reference outputs from force:true to freeze_policy:checksum, leaving only their own mod_wiring exception file, confirmed by direct read of every template in both packs. Verified via composed_packs_e2e's real 2/2 pass (all 10 fixed packs are in its 30-pack composed set). Deliberately DEFERRED, not sampled: level-five-book-pack -- its 70+ raw force:true grep hits are almost entirely book:sourceText prose (a book chapter literally titled 'force and Regeneration' teaching the concept, embedded as ontology literal content, not template frontmatter); its 2 real templates (chapter.md.tmpl, listing.tmpl) use a dynamic per-row `to: \"src/{{ path }}\"` target generating one file per book:Chapter/book:Listing individual (366+366), a materially different write-semantics shape than every other pack sampled so far and not yet composed_packs_e2e-verified in this configuration -- needs its own dedicated pass, not folded into this one. ggen-verify-pack (6 occurrences) also deferred: excluded from composed_packs_e2e by the test's own module doc (refuses to sync without consumer-provided ver: evidence facts a hermetic consumer won't fabricate), so the established verification path doesn't cover it -- needs a dedicated scratch-consumer test, not a bulk assumption. Remaining, NOT closed: 8 force:true occurrences across exactly these 2 deferred packs." ;
    ctl:verificationRequirement "cargo test -p ggen-engine --test cross_pack_matrix mega_project_all_packs_sync; cd examples/tcps-generated && cargo test --test tcps_conformance_e2e -- real runs, 2026-07-21." .

ctl:O-6-hygiene a ctl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:label "Repository structural hygiene: 124 root files (~95 violations), orphaned templates/ (491 files), examples/archive/ 1547 tracked files" ;
    ctl:priority 15 ;
    ctl:state ctl:READY ;
    ctl:nextAction "Lowest priority tier by design -- independently recounted 2026-07-21, real but must not displace O-3/O-4/O-5/AP-001. Deletion via reviewed PR with a full deletion ledger when picked up, not a silent rm." .

ctl:O-8 a ctl:Obligation ;
    rdfs:label "composed_packs_e2e::thirty_one_packs_compose_with_verify_gates_active -- RETRACTED, false positive" ;
    ctl:priority 1 ;
    ctl:state ctl:CLOSED ;
    ctl:nextAction "RETRACTED 2026-07-21, same cycle it was opened: re-run after this cycle's cargo clean + fresh rebuild (target/debug/ggen rebuilt via cargo build -p ggen-cli-lib --bin ggen) -- the test now PASSES cleanly ('test result: ok. 1 passed'). Root cause of the original failure: a STALE cached test binary (CliHarness::cargo_bin(\"ggen\") locating an out-of-date target/debug/ggen built before some source change, not a live code defect). The original 'confirmed pre-existing via git stash' check was itself run against that same stale environment, so it wrongly corroborated a false positive rather than actually isolating anything. Correction applied per re-derivation discipline: do not let a wrong finding stand once the corrected premise (fresh binary, real pass) is in hand. [law].reflexive genuinely exists on GgenConfig::Law (crates/ggen-engine/src/config.rs:98) and this fixture's ggen.toml correctly classifies as Frontmatter and parses -- independently re-verified via two isolated repro attempts before the real re-run confirmed it." .
